Nothing at all. I'm sorry I shouted.

956
01:27:30,158 --> 01:27:32,319
Mr. Valentine,
you've got to see this my way.

957
01:27:32,393 --> 01:27:35,658
I'm the First Officer of an airplane
in a severe storm.

958
01:27:35,730 --> 01:27:37,493
Now, I have an irrational passenger.

959
01:27:37,565 --> 01:27:39,226
You're threatening the safety
of this aircraft

960
01:27:39,334 --> 01:27:41,325
and you're frightening
the other passengers.

961
01:27:41,402 --> 01:27:43,870
You either calm down
or we're gonna handcuff you.

962
01:27:43,938 --> 01:27:46,668
Listen, there's something wrong
with this airplane!

963
01:27:46,741 --> 01:27:47,867
I don't care what happens to me,

964
01:27:47,942 --> 01:27:51,503
but if somebody doesn't do something
about it, we're all gonna die!

965
01:27:52,447 --> 01:27:55,883
- That's D-I-E, die!
- You big silly!

966
01:27:55,950 --> 01:27:57,941
You used to be a normal person!

967
01:27:58,052 --> 01:27:59,849
Sit down, darling. Come on, okay?

968
01:27:59,921 --> 01:28:04,881
Mr. Valentine, what do you think
is wrong with this aircraft?

969
01:28:07,628 --> 01:28:10,563
- There's an engine out.
- Which one?

970
01:28:11,232 --> 01:28:13,359
The one on the outside.

971
01:28:13,434 --> 01:28:16,232
Outboard number one. It's out, isn't it?

972
01:28:17,138 --> 01:28:21,302
- What makes you think that?
- Never mind about that. It's true, isn't it?

973
01:28:22,410 --> 01:28:25,038
Nine minutes ago, outboard number one
was struck by lightning.

974
01:28:25,113 --> 01:28:26,444
There was a flame-out, and we lost it.

975
01:28:26,547 --> 01:28:28,811
- Lightning.
- Lightning.

976
01:28:30,985 --> 01:28:34,580
Mr. Valentine,
this aircraft has four engines.

977
01:28:34,655 --> 01:28:37,954
The possibility of us losing one of the
remaining three is remote in the extreme.

978
01:28:38,059 --> 01:28:40,323
You're sure it was just lightning?

979
01:28:42,096 --> 01:28:43,461
Absolutely.

980
01:28:46,401 --> 01:28:50,167
Listen, we're gonna be landing
in about 20 minutes.

981
01:28:51,839 --> 01:28:56,003
There is the highest probability
that we'll survive this flight.

982
01:28:57,645 --> 01:28:58,669
Okay.

983
01:29:03,985 --> 01:29:08,115
We'll see you downstairs in 20 minutes.
Sit down. Buckle them up!

984
01:29:12,360 --> 01:29:13,952
Are you okay?

985
01:29:41,122 --> 01:29:43,454
No, no, no, no.

986
01:29:50,798 --> 01:29:51,890
I love you.

987
01:29:51,999 --> 01:29:54,467
Hail Mary, full of grace,
the Lord is with thee...

988
01:30:37,111 --> 01:30:39,341
Mommy. Mommy. Mommy.

989
01:30:41,883 --> 01:30:45,842
What are you doing now?
That's very bad manners, you know!

990
01:30:46,587 --> 01:30:51,251
- Didn't anyone ever teach you manners?
- Come on. Come on.

991
01:31:00,434 --> 01:31:01,731
God damn!

992
01:31:37,772 --> 01:31:39,740
He's got a gun!

993
01:33:14,702 --> 01:33:19,935
And that's exactly how it happened.
I'm practically a hero.

994
01:33:20,675 --> 01:33:21,937
Would you believe that?

995
01:33:22,043 --> 01:33:26,173
Weather broke, we would
never have gotten this baby down.

996
01:33:26,247 --> 01:33:28,044
A hell of a night.

997
01:33:28,115 --> 01:33:31,949
We got the storm, we got the flame-out,
and then that freak show.

998
01:33:32,053 --> 01:33:35,386
Not to mention the gun.
The gun was awful.

999
01:33:35,456 --> 01:33:39,256
He didn't have a gun. No, no, no,
he didn't have a gun. It was my gun.

1000
01:33:39,360 --> 01:33:41,385
It was my gun. I'm FAA.
I'm authorized to have a gun.

1001
01:33:41,462 --> 01:33:45,796
He was so crazy. He smashed the window.
What was he trying to do? Get out?

1002
01:33:45,900 --> 01:33:49,233
It's claustrophobia! They'd rather fall
to the ground than stay aboard.

1003
01:33:49,303 --> 01:33:52,295
I've seen it happen. I've seen it!

1004
01:33:52,406 --> 01:33:54,806
I knew he was frightened,
but I didn't think he was crazy.

1005
01:33:54,909 --> 01:33:57,434
But, Dionne,
he said he saw something on the wing.

1006
01:33:57,545 --> 01:34:00,275
Max, we lost number one.
Check out number two, will you?

1007
01:34:01,549 --> 01:34:03,813
All right. Somebody give me a light.
I want the gear pin.

1008
01:34:03,918 --> 01:34:05,442
Let's check these tires.

1009
01:34:05,553 --> 01:34:08,420
Franco, let me know
what's going on with these flaps.

1010
01:34:08,489 --> 01:34:11,481
I want to know if there's any fuel
leaking out of this baby.

1011
01:34:11,592 --> 01:34:13,753
And get these people out of here.

1012
01:34:25,272 --> 01:34:28,764
Max! Max! Max!

1013
01:34:32,346 --> 01:34:34,405
Holy Toledo!

1014
01:34:34,482 --> 01:34:37,417
Hey, you guys, what happened up there?

1015
01:34:49,330 --> 01:34:51,594
That's enough of that noise, huh?

1016
01:34:51,665 --> 01:34:54,930
Who needs it anyway?
How about a little music?

1017
01:34:55,002 --> 01:34:56,264
Sure.

1018
01:35:03,711 --> 01:35:06,839
Hey, that's... That's...

1019
01:35:08,382 --> 01:35:10,612
I love Creedence.

1020
01:35:12,186 --> 01:35:14,677
So you had a big scare up there, huh?

1021
01:35:15,356 --> 01:35:16,823
Oh, yeah.

1022
01:35:18,192 --> 01:35:20,626
Want to see something really scary?

1023
01:35:28,402 --> 01:35:32,964
<i>There is a fifth dimension
beyond that which is known to man.</i>

1024
01:35:33,040 --> 01:35:36,532
<i>It is the middle ground
between light and shadow,</i>

1025
01:35:36,644 --> 01:35:38,874
<i>between science and superstition,</i>

1026
01:35:38,979 --> 01:35:44,884
<i>and it lies between the pit of man's fears
and the summit of his knowledge.</i>

1027
01:35:44,985 --> 01:35:47,180
<i>This is the dimension of imagination.</i>

1028
01:35:47,254 --> 01:35:50,690
<i>It is an area which we call
the Twilight Zone.</i>

1029
01:41:09,476 --> 01:41:10,500
English - SDH

